Patch Set 2:

The change itself looks good to me.

But when I check the in-tree doc [0], I noticed the glance_store code has a different default value with the doc. So I think we could update one to make them be consistent by a separated patch, probable updating code to use s3.amazonaws.com seems a good idea to me, then we will replace 127.0.0.1 with s3.amazonaws.com at config sample files as well.

[0] https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/doc/source/configuring.rst

Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

Without this change glance_store s3 driver will get failure.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

Can you explain why the default in conf is 127.0.0.1 yet in doc/source/configuring.rst it is referenced as s3.amazonaws.com?  Should the commit message to this have a DocImpact tag?
